  "description": [
    "PUPILS RECITAL Dorothy Wright and Carol Noteboom presented their pu pils in a joint Recital in Zion Conservatory Hall on Monday evening June 13th at 800 P M rendering a very pleasing evenings program of voice and piano selections Even though the evening was exceptionally warm a goodly number of parents rel atives and friends came out to encourage the pupils and the teachers all of whom spent many hours of toil in order to HONOR DAUGHTER After the Commencement Exercises of Zion Conserva tory of Music last Friday evening Mr and Mrs Wilbur Ball of 2529 Elizabeth Ave honored their daughter Val erie with a social gathering of relatives and invited guests Mrs Lucille Sparrow a for mer resident of Zion and Val eries aunt flew from San attain the perfection which was so evident on this interest ing and artistic Recital Leandro California near Oakland to be present at the Commeincement Mrs Spar row will be well remembered by listeners to Zions Radio Station WCBD as a contralto soloist and with Zion Choir She returned last Friday by plane Railroad workers achieved the 8hour day in 1916 by an act of Congress making it ef fective on railroads"
